[{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Author = \"Adam H. Sparks\"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Epicrop.jl is a Julia package that can be used to simulate disease epidemics. If you have not yet installed Julia, please follow the instructions for your operating system.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"This package provides a Healthy-Latent-Infectious-Postinfectious (HLIP) model for unmanaged plant disease epidemic modelling. Originally this modelling framework was used by specific disease models in EPIRICE to simulate severity of several rice diseases (Savary et al. 2012). Given proper values it can be used with other pathosystems as well.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"-","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Epicrop.jl is not yet a registered Julia package, but I hope to have it in good enough condition to register it shortly. Until then you can install it with the following commands:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> using Pkg\n\njulia> Pkg.clone(\"https://github.com/adamhsparks/Epicrop.jl\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Modules = [Epicrop]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"-","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Modules = [Epicrop]\nOrder   = [:module]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Types","page":"-","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Modules = [Epicrop]\nOrder   = [:type]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Methods","page":"-","title":"Methods","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Modules = [Epicrop]\nOrder   = [:function]","category":"page"}]
